Vendored dependency: Tesseract.js (and Tesseract.js-core)
Version: 5.1.1
License: Apache License 2.0
Homepage: https://github.com/naptha/tesseract.js
Homepage (core): https://github.com/naptha/tesseract.js-core

Files vendored under js/vendor/:
  tesseract.min.js            — main API (dist/tesseract.min.js)
  worker.min.js                — worker script (dist/worker.min.js)
  tesseract-core-lstm.wasm.js  — WebAssembly OCR engine glue (LSTM-only build)
  tesseract-core-lstm.wasm     — WebAssembly OCR engine binary (LSTM-only build)

Language data vendored under assets/ocr/:
  eng.traineddata.gz — English trained data (LSTM "best_int" model), sourced
  from the tesseract.js-data distribution, itself derived from the Tesseract
  OCR project's tessdata_fast/tessdata_best models (Apache License 2.0).

These files are committed unmodified (Protocol 39 UTF-8/binary integrity) and
self-hosted so the app never depends on a third-party CDN at runtime (CSP:
script-src/worker-src 'self'). See https://github.com/naptha/tesseract.js/blob/master/LICENSE.md
and https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/tessdata_fast for upstream license text.

